cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.DS

The paper proposes a method to identify influential nodes in complex networks using statistical mechanics and degree centrality. The evaluation of the method is done using the Susceptible-Infective (SI) model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the local structure of the network, which can be related to the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Development and Programming). The use of statistical mechanics suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control), while the focus on identifying influential nodes can be related to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
